headline: 3 of Wall Street’s Favorite Stocks We’re Skeptical Of
summary: Wall Street is overwhelmingly bullish on the stocks in this article, with price targets suggesting significant upside potential. However, it’s worth remembering that analysts rarely issue sell ratings, partly because their firms often seek other business from the same companies they cover.

headline: Hormel Foods (HRL): Assessing Value After Recent Share Price Weakness
summary: Hormel Foods (HRL) shares have been under steady pressure lately, trailing lower over the past month. Investors are weighing recent numbers and considering the broader market's appetite for consumer staples as they watch for new drivers. See our latest analysis for Hormel Foods. Hormel's share price has taken a hit in 2024, sliding over 24% year-to-date and losing more than 21% in total shareholder return over the past year.
